description:

Two floor Georgian Apartment with a double bedroom for rent, new renovation in Bloomsbury, the heart of London. This apt has all amenities you need plus a small outdoor deck / garden. Despite the central location the apt is very quiet, especially at evenings and weekends.

This apartment has WIFI internet, a washer and dryer, iron and ironing board, wardrobe and drawers for your clothes, a fully equipped kitchen with dishwasher, separate dining room, the bathroom has a walk in shower and underfloor heating, movies and through room music system available. The cleaning fee is £41 for each week you stay. I will adjust this when it comes to you booking.
neighborhood_overview: Plenty of award winning restaurants and pubs nearby on Exmouth Market, Clerkenwell Rd, Lambs Conduit Street and St. John's Street. The British Museum is on the other side of Russell Sq, the West End and Soho all within a 20 minute walk. Shoreditch, East London's new art district is close, with galleries, boutiques and restaurants, and is a 20 minute bus ride. The Tate and the South Bank is a 20 minute bus ride to the river.

description:
Beautiful double room in Barons Court, West London, mansion block flat. Quiet street, one minute from tube, great local shops, green space behind, Queens club, river-walks nearby. Easy access to central London, Notting Hill, Kensington, & airports.

The space
We have a beautiful double room available in our spacious mansion block flat. The well-equipped kitchen dinning room is light and airy. There's a bathroom with a toilet, and a separate shower room, as well as a second toilet.
There's always plenty of hot water any time of day or night.

We're an artistic household of music, painting, film and theatre makers, happy to give pointers on current cultural events. I also offer acting/writing/directing/creativity workshops.

Guest access
Kitchen-dinning room, shower-room, bathroom, toilets.
High speed broadband internet.

Guests can use the dishwasher, washing machine and dryer within reason.

We will
neighborhood_overview:
Barons Court is a bit of a hidden gem. It's leafy, quiet, and safe with brilliant transport access to other more lively areas and the airports.

The legendary Queen's tennis club is actually on our street. In case you don't know, Queens is a beautiful old tennis club, and the venue for a pre-Wimbledon tournament that takes place every summer.

Easy travel to Heathrow (about 30mins on Picadilly line), and proximity to the roads out of London, make this area a great place if you are commuting into London for work.
It's also a great base for exploring other areas such as Notting Hill, Portobello (Portobello Market), Kensington (the Natural History museum, Science museum, V&A museum). We're about 15/20 mins from the West End (theatres) Covent Garden (Royal Opera and shopping) and Soho, and perhaps 40 from Kings Cross and east London.

There are lovely shops in the neighborhood, an incredible organic/free range butchers, a French cafe for croissants an
host_about:
I am an actor, musician, and teacher living in London, but traveling quite a lot with my band and acting work. 
I love music, books, theater, learning, walking in the hills, swimming in the ocean, cycling, yoga, meditation, feasting, very dark chocolate, laughter, good conversation, and too many other things to list here.

I love having friends stay at my place and helping them to discover this fantastic city. I've lived in London a long time and go out to a lot of music and theater so can recommend quite a few interesting places to visit.
We have a nice, big kitchen at home so enjoy cooking together and having friends round for dinner but the flat is not a party scene. 
The apartment building itself is a lovely, peaceful mansion block backing onto green space.

We are an Anglo-Irish family who have been living in La Rochelle since 2003. We manage holiday accommodation here, in a super town for tourists and those seeking to get away from the bustle of life. In addition, we are musicians and we sing, write and play together in a band called The Portraits.

neighborhood_overview:
De Beauvoir is a lovely neighbourhood located between Shoreditch, Hoxton and Dalston. You can easily walk to many restaurants, bars and enjoy the canal and local parks.

The broader area of Hackney surrounds De Beauvoir. There's plenty of heart in Hackney, where high art and edgy innovation meet. There are flavours to savour from its lip-smacking restaurants, not to mention world-class coffees, quirky, scruffy, sleek or hip – the area's bars and pubs suit whatever taste you're packing, as do its diversions (you're seriously spoilt for things to do). And if money's still burning a hole, Hackney's shops and markets sell temptation by the truckload, from vintage fabrics and designer must-haves to rare meats and artisanal bread.

Child's Hill is a quaint neighbourhood nestled between the charming areas of Hampstead, Golders Green, and Finchley Road. It's remarkably peaceful at night, and during the day, you might encounter a bit of passing traffic.

For your daily grocery needs, you'll find a conveniently located Co-Op, along with a couple of smaller shops that stay open later for added convenience.

If you're a fan of cafes and restaurants, you're in luck. There are some delightful options just a stone's throw away.

I'd highly recommend exploring Golders Green, especially for its restaurant scene. One standout choice is L'Artista, known for its authentic and affordably priced Italian cuisine.

For a refreshing escape from the bustling streets of London, consider taking a leisurely 10-minute stroll to reach the serene haven of Hampstead Heath. It's a perfect retreat for nature lovers and a great way to unwind amidst the city's hustle and bustle.

host_about:
Hi! Hello! Salut! Hola! Ciao! Ni Hao! Привет!

My name is Roman, before UK I used to live in US, Hungary, Slovakia and Ukraine.  I am an Engineer by education, Chef by passion and Entrepreneur by spirit.  I was engaged in a number of projects across different fields of interest, and I've lived in London since 2015.  Living here is very challenging but also very rewarding in many ways.  London is an amazing city and I want all the guests to experience the diverse beat and spirit that London has to offer. 

I enjoy traveling a lot but I enjoy hosting even more.  I like everything that is part of a peer-to-peer sharing economy.  Empty rooms, parked cars, unused tools, even dusty books, all of these can be made to work for other people and reward those whom it belongs to. 

So I'm helping people I know or have been recommended to in running their properties when they're away or busy with other things.  I enjoy engaging with travelers, answering questions, and providing some local info and advice. 

My other interests include cooking, hiking, kayaking, cycling and motorcycling, with lots of trips by foot, wheels and pedals already accomplished and many more to come.  Not to forget gardening and wild herbs and fungi foraging for my fusion recipes. 

I would be very happy to meet you in London and make sure that your stay is comfortable and enjoyable. 

Cheers!

neighborhood_overview:
At first glance, the street looks unremarkable. Over the years I have grown to love that it's on a Close (and therefore quiet most of the time), and near to some truly excellent spots. A short bus ride can get you to wonderful Walthamstow, Stratford, Dalston, the Olympic Park, the Central line... and from there anywhere you like. included in the photos for this listing are some favourite local attractions.

Off the top of my head, some favourites local places are: God's Own Junkyard, Mother's Ruin Gin Palace, Walthamstow Wetlands, The Clock (where they bake their goods right next door, the smell alone is.... *chef's kiss), the modest but very cute Jubilee Park, Orford Road, Leyton Technical, one of the UK's two(!) Uygher restaurants, the maze in Coronation Gardens, a few handfuls of excellent coffee shops, booksellers and wine bars.

The thing to note, I suppose, is that all of London is at your door step here.

The space
You will be staying in a classy London neighbourhood surrounded by original Victorian architecture while getting around very easily. Kitchen and living area has all modern appliances, 2 sofas, fireplace, TV & Internet access.

Complimentary
neighborhood_overview:
Battersea is located on the south bank of the Thames, close to Fulham and Chelsea.
It is full of beautiful Victorian architecture and a lovely park where you will experience the joys of riverside living.

If you like the 'different' and you are fan of the river, there are so many interesting things to do, walking distance from the flat. Buckingham Palace for example is only 45 min walk. Only locals know that!

Just a hint; why dine in a regular, land-locked restaurant when you could enjoy a floating one? Battersea Barge is a restored 1930s Dutch boat with a past that includes transporting Hitler’s tanks during the Second World War, but now enjoys a much calmer occupation as a bar and bistro restaurant with regular music, comedy and cabaret nights. Perhaps not one for the sea sick though!

London is the Europe's top choice for the most interesting things to do! No matter what you fancy, I am sure you will find in London!
